{
  "video_id": "cN7sZ2wMg_Q",
  "title": "Ballagàrraidh: The Awareness That You Are Not at Home in the Wilderness",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 1400.0,
      "end_time": 3250.0,
      "text": "Sometimes you move through the city"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 3250.0,
      "end_time": 6620.0,
      "text": "and feel in your bones how strange and new this all is."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6620.0,
      "end_time": 10280.0,
      "text": "The spectacle of modern civilization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 10280.0,
      "end_time": 12940.0,
      "text": "just barely older than you are."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 12940.0,
      "end_time": 15480.0,
      "text": "With all its cramped logic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15480.0,
      "end_time": 17289.0,
      "text": "its rules and gridlines and"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 17289.0,
      "end_time": 21390.0,
      "text": "rigid justifications for why the world must be the way it is."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 21390.0,
      "end_time": 23830.0,
      "text": "But there's a part of you that thinks:"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 23830.0,
      "end_time": 25359.0,
      "text": "you are not at home here."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 25359.0,
      "end_time": 27179.0,
      "text": "That still remembers Eden,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 27179.0,
      "end_time": 30359.0,
      "text": "and longs to return."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 30359.0,
      "end_time": 34040.0,
      "text": "Ballagàrraidh."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 34040.0,
      "end_time": 38660.0,
      "text": "The story of humanity is a move from the countryside to the big city."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 38660.0,
      "end_time": 44690.0,
      "text": "But it's happening so fast that our brains are still stuck in the hinterlands."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 44690.0,
      "end_time": 48010.0,
      "text": "So now there's a part of you that longs to leave your car idling in traffic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 48010.0,
      "end_time": 50720.0,
      "text": "and flee into the wilderness."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 50720.0,
      "end_time": 52940.0,
      "text": "To live off the land,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 52940.0,
      "end_time": 55540.0,
      "text": "without tools or simulations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 55540.0,
      "end_time": 58640.0,
      "text": "to experience nature in all its simplicity"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 58640.0,
      "end_time": 62780.0,
      "text": "raw, indifferent, and ferociously real."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 62780.0,
      "end_time": 65790.0,
      "text": "To feel the lushness and harshness of the wild,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 65790.0,
      "end_time": 69770.0,
      "text": "the clarity of eating and killing and growing stronger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 69770.0,
      "end_time": 73400.0,
      "text": "the dumb luck of surviving the night."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 73400.0,
      "end_time": 76140.0,
      "text": "But another part of you knows that Eden is a fantasy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 76140.0,
      "end_time": 78800.0,
      "text": "and you'll always be floating just above it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 78800.0,
      "end_time": 82290.0,
      "text": "trailing clouds of civilization wherever you go."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 82290.0,
      "end_time": 85450.0,
      "text": "Even our ancient symbols of nature are deeply unnatural."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 85450.0,
      "end_time": 91930.0,
      "text": "The plants we eat are sterile, swollen, unrecognizable to the food chain."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 91930.0,
      "end_time": 97000.0,
      "text": "Our domesticated animals are caricatures of their wild ancestors."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 97000.0,
      "end_time": 100460.0,
      "text": "The family dog is just another piece of technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 100460.0,
      "end_time": 103240.0,
      "text": "And you too are a domesticated animal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 103240.0,
      "end_time": 107070.0,
      "text": "shrouded in synthetic fibers and synthetic thoughts."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 107070.0,
      "end_time": 110710.0,
      "text": "Even if you sleep in the woods with a stove and a backpack,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 110710.0,
      "end_time": 112500.0,
      "text": "everything from the buzzing in your ears"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 112500.0,
      "end_time": 114120.0,
      "text": "to the howling in the distance"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 114120.0,
      "end_time": 115990.0,
      "text": "will be trying to tell you:"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 115990.0,
      "end_time": 119369.0,
      "text": "you are not at home here."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 119369.0,
      "end_time": 121710.0,
      "text": "We need to believe in the fall from Eden."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 121710.0,
      "end_time": 126280.0,
      "text": "But all along, we were the ones who cast out the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 126280.0,
      "end_time": 127610.0,
      "text": "Who stripped it naked,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 127610.0,
      "end_time": 129330.0,
      "text": "taught it good and evil,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 129330.00000000001,
      "end_time": 133280.0,
      "text": "and barricaded ourselves in a walled garden."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 133280.0,
      "end_time": 135690.0,
      "text": "We couldn't handle the true state of nature—"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 135690.0,
      "end_time": 138029.0,
      "text": "the overwhelming chaos—"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 138029.0,
      "end_time": 140829.0,
      "text": "without first dividing it up into little boxes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 140829.0,
      "end_time": 143719.0,
      "text": "in little gardens."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 143719.0,
      "end_time": 146920.0,
      "text": "Maybe we were wrong from the start."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 146920.0,
      "end_time": 148159.0,
      "text": "In the beginning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 148159.0,
      "end_time": 158159.0,
      "text": "there was everything."
    }
  ]
}